# 🚗 Car Purchase Prediction (Regression Analysis)

## 🔍 Overview

This project analyzes customer financial data to predict car purchase amounts using regression techniques.

## 🎯 Objective

To identify key financial factors influencing car purchase decisions and build a predictive regression model.

## 📁 Dataset

* Features:

  * Annual Salary (AS)
  * Net Worth (NW)
  * Credit Card Debt (CCD)
* Target Variable:

  * Car Purchase Amount

## 🧹 Data Preprocessing

* Outliers detected and treated across all variables
* Data normalization checked
* Multicollinearity analyzed using VIF

## 📊 Exploratory Data Analysis

* Strong correlation observed:

  * Annual Salary & Car Purchase Amount (0.62)
  * Net Worth & Car Purchase Amount 
* Scatter plots showed clear linear trends for salary

## 🤖 Model Used

* Multiple Linear Regression (OLS)

## 📈 Model Performance

* R² Score: **0.607**
* Adjusted R²: **0.605**
* Model is statistically significant (p < 0.05)

## 🔑 Key Insights

* Significant predictors:

  * Annual Salary
  * Net Worth
* Insignificant variable:

  * Credit Card Debt

## 📊 Statistical Validation

* Residuals are normally distributed
* No autocorrelation (Durbin-Watson ≈ 2)
* Model assumptions satisfied

## 📁 Files Included

* Dataset (CSV)
* Python analysis code
* Final report (PDF)

